load_data¶

PostgreSQL load helpers for admissions JSONL data.

load_data.create_db_if_not_exists()[source]¶

Create the grad_data database when unmanaged local defaults are used.

If DATABASE_URL is explicitly set, provisioning is assumed to be managed externally and this function exits immediately.

Returns:

None.

Return type:

None

load_data.get_max_result_page()[source]¶

Fetch the highest ingested GradCafe result-page number.

Returns:

Maximum result_page value, or None if unavailable.

Return type:

int | None

load_data.get_existing_urls()[source]¶

Fetch all existing admissions URLs currently stored in PostgreSQL.

Returns:

Set of unique URL strings, or empty set on connection/query error.

Return type:

set[str]

load_data.format_date(date_str)[source]¶

Convert date text to a date object compatible with PostgreSQL.

Parameters:

date_str (str | None) – Date string in '%B %d, %Y' format.

Returns:

Parsed date or None when missing/invalid.

Return type:

datetime.date | None

load_data.stream_jsonl_to_postgres(filepath)[source]¶

Stream JSONL records into PostgreSQL admissions table.

The function creates the target table/index when needed, inserts rows with ON CONFLICT (url) DO NOTHING, and commits once all valid records are processed.

Parameters:

filepath (str) – Path to line-delimited JSON records.

Returns:

None.

Return type:

None

Raises:

Exception – Propagates unexpected filesystem or database errors.
